main event: A series of unidentified flying objects were observed in Los Angeles on March 19, 1967.
interesting points: The objects were in sight for approximately 15 minutes,Observers described the objects as bright and moving in a formation,The report lacked sufficient data for scientific evaluation,The witness had prior service in the Air Force and was an architect,At least one other person (the witness's wife) was present during the sighting.
sighted object: three bright objects in the sky
witness description: A 36-year-old male, former Air Force service member and architect
